x4freetext: Targets were made by evaporating natural metallic Ge
on thin, high purity Al foils.
The thickness of the targets varied between 50 and 290
ug/cm2, corresponding to a proton energy loss of
~2 keV at Ep=4.4 MeV and ~25 keV at Ep=1.6 MeV,
Rutherford backscattering (RBS) was used to monitor
the target stability with a surface barrier detector
Faraday cup was used to collect the charge using a
proton beam current less than 500 nA.
Secondary electron suppression was used with -300 V.
Measurements started 0.5 h after end of irradiations.
The energy loss was calculated using the SRIM code.
Cross sections and astrophysical S factor were derived
Reaction Rates were calculated from the measured data.
